div.div: There may be alignments in the directions across multiple vector spaces

Depending on the definition of direction & the position of vectors, this may indicate similarity in intent (if multiple intents defined this way align, they may be interchangeable, similar, or composable if adjacent intent networks are semantically related).

There are patterns in intent types: if multiple intents in a stack or chain are neutral, that signals a malicious intent, when the sum or combination of the intents are graphed on the intent network space to indicate intent type.
Since intents can have multiple sub-intents from multiple perspective filters, each vector can map to another space where its stack or network of sub-intents is depicted.
